Example usage

Here we demonstrate how to use Financial Analyzer to calcuate financial metrics like ROI, breakeven point, and sale units needed to output desirable profit. This package can also produces visualization of the cost, revenue, and breakeven point/

Import

from financial_analyzer.breakeven_point import breakeven_point
from financial_analyzer.roi import roi
from financial_analyzer.units_for_target_profit import units_for_target_profit
from financial_analyzer.plot_breakeven_point import plot_breakeven_point

Initialize sample data

investment = 1000
target_profit = 1200

fixed_cost = 200
sales_price_per_unit = 1
variable_cost_per_unit = 0.5
max_unit = 1000

Breakeven point calculation

Returns the breakeven point where the revenue and cost add up tp be 0

breakeven_point(fixed_cost, sales_price_per_unit, variable_cost_per_unit)

400.0

Return On Investment calculation

Calcuate the percentage return on investment

roi(investment, target_profit)

20.0

Target Unit Calculation

Calculate the unit to reach the target profit

units_for_target_profit(fixed_cost, sales_price_per_unit, variable_cost_per_unit, target_profit)

2800

Breakeven Poin Visualization

This function create a visualization that shows the relationship between unit sale, total cost, and revenue. It also highlights the breakeven point.

plot, _ = plot_breakeven_point(fixed_cost, sales_price_per_unit, variable_cost_per_unit, max_unit)
plot
